AngularJS has its own HTML events(user events) directives.
We can add one or more of these event directives to HTML elements.

ng-blur       -
ng-change
ng-click
ng-copy
ng-cut
ng-dblclick
ng-focus
ng-keydown
ng-keypress
ng-keyup

Mouse Events - Mouse events occur when the cursor moves over an element, order
    1. ng-mouseover
    2. ng-mouseenter
    3. ng-mousemove
    4. ng-mouseleave

Or when a mouse button is clicked on an element, order
    1. ng-mousedown
    2. ng-mouseup
    3. ng-paste


$event Object
    The $event object contains the browser's event object